WEBVTT

00:04.129 --> 00:06.048
<i>‐Previously...</i>
<i>‐On</i> The Affair...

00:06.131 --> 00:08.717
[Joanie] <i>I found some sort</i>
<i>of shrine at Dad's.</i>

00:08.800 --> 00:09.593
What did you do with it?

00:09.676 --> 00:11.720
I threw it out.

00:11.803 --> 00:12.429
Why?

00:12.513 --> 00:15.641
Because I hate looking at her.

00:15.724 --> 00:18.227
Two astronauts meet by chance in
the International Space Station.

00:18.310 --> 00:22.064
<i>They fall desperately in love,</i>
<i>but their love is doomed.</i>

00:22.147 --> 00:23.899
<i>They try to forget each other.</i>
<i>They build completely</i>

00:23.982 --> 00:25.150
<i>new lives with new people.</i>

00:25.234 --> 00:29.112
<i>But, deep down, they</i>
<i>secretly still love each other.</i>

00:29.196 --> 00:31.031
<i>Until one day, they run</i>
<i>into each other again</i>

00:31.114 --> 00:33.825
<i>on the opposite side</i>
<i>of the galaxy.</i>

00:33.909 --> 00:36.245
<i>Because all this time</i>

00:36.328 --> 00:38.330
<i>they thought they were moving</i>
<i>away from each other,</i>

00:38.413 --> 00:40.457
they were
actually in orbit.

00:40.541 --> 00:42.000
I love you.

00:42.084 --> 00:43.627
I don't want your love.

00:43.710 --> 00:46.004
It terrifies me,
and it's caused me

00:46.088 --> 00:47.256
nothing but pain.

00:47.339 --> 00:48.840
[Whitney] <i>We can't afford</i>
<i>a wedding, can we?</i>

00:48.924 --> 00:50.759
Come on, Whitney.
You've been talking

00:50.842 --> 00:51.843
about having a wedding
in this house

00:51.927 --> 00:53.762
since before you were in braces.

00:53.845 --> 00:55.931
Okay, I just received
the last part of my advance,

00:56.014 --> 00:57.474
and I can't think of
a better thing to spend it on.

00:57.557 --> 00:59.726
I used to think, when we had no
money and we had all these kids

00:59.810 --> 01:01.436
and we were fighting,
I would look at you sometimes

01:01.520 --> 01:04.106
and I would think, "One day,
this is gonna be worth it.

01:04.189 --> 01:07.276
One day, I'm gonna dance
with him at Whitney's wedding."

01:07.359 --> 01:08.485
I saw the way

01:08.569 --> 01:10.195
you look at women.

01:10.279 --> 01:11.947
Like they're prey.

01:12.030 --> 01:14.283
How the fuck did you not know
it was her in the hot tub?!

01:14.366 --> 01:17.744
I would do anything‐‐ anything‐‐
to undo what happened!

01:17.828 --> 01:20.122
If I can just give her
a good wedding,

01:20.205 --> 01:22.291
with us all there together,
having fun, then‐‐

01:22.374 --> 01:24.626
She doesn't want you there.

01:24.710 --> 01:28.088
Jesus Christ.

01:36.430 --> 01:39.558
<i>♪ I was screaming</i>
<i>into the canyon ♪</i>

01:39.641 --> 01:41.852
<i>♪ At the moment of my death ♪</i>

01:41.935 --> 01:46.106
<i>♪ The echo I created ♪</i>

01:46.189 --> 01:49.192
<i>♪ Outlasted my last breath ♪</i>

01:49.276 --> 01:52.571
<i>♪ My voice it made</i>
<i>an avalanche ♪</i>

01:52.654 --> 01:55.615
<i>♪ And buried a man</i>
<i>I never knew ♪</i>

01:55.699 --> 01:58.827
<i>♪ And when he died,</i>
<i>his widowed bride ♪</i>

01:58.910 --> 02:01.496
<i>♪ Met your daddy</i>
<i>and they made you ♪</i>

02:01.580 --> 02:03.415
<i>♪ I have only one thing to do ♪</i>

02:03.498 --> 02:04.833
<i>♪ And that's be the wave</i>
<i>that I am, and then ♪</i>

02:04.916 --> 02:08.045
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

02:08.128 --> 02:10.172
<i>♪ I have only one thing to do ♪</i>

02:10.255 --> 02:12.507
<i>♪ And that's be the wave</i>
