Whitney's wedding right now.

44:37.925 --> 44:40.678
And it does feel like
a familiar pattern between us

44:40.761 --> 44:42.555
where I get exiled
and you come rescue me.

44:42.638 --> 44:45.224
And we know how that ends.
Don't we?

44:48.728 --> 44:50.271
But I'm not saying
you've got a pathology

44:50.354 --> 44:52.732
or anything wrong
with you.

44:55.735 --> 44:59.530
But even if we do
love each other, it...

45:01.282 --> 45:04.785
...doesn't mean
we're good for each other.

45:09.373 --> 45:09.916
[sighs]

45:09.999 --> 45:12.418
What does that mean...

45:12.501 --> 45:14.545
"good for each other"?

45:14.629 --> 45:16.756
Well, I think certain couples

45:16.839 --> 45:19.300
have hurt each other less
than we have.

45:23.429 --> 45:25.723
I think certain couples

45:25.806 --> 45:28.517
have loved each other less
than we have, too.

45:33.189 --> 45:35.149
True.

45:42.698 --> 45:45.785
I mean, what's the endgame here?

45:45.868 --> 45:48.663
We're just supposed to get old
and lose our‐our...

45:48.746 --> 45:51.374
hearing and our hair...

45:51.457 --> 45:54.335
our memory, and then we die?

45:56.212 --> 45:59.048
I guess so.

46:06.097 --> 46:08.599
You know, I know the story
I'm supposed to tell

46:08.683 --> 46:12.311
